/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. For the sake of brevity, this siddur omits the traditional
second /ITAmidah/XX recited on Shabbat and Festivals. This /ITMusaf/XX (additional)
/ITAmidah/XX, which emphasizes the additional sacrifices offered on Shabbat and
Festivals during the time of the first and second Temple, had its own
/ITKedushah/XX. In order to avoid losing the words and melody of the /ITMusaf
Kedushah/XX, it has been incorporated here into the /ITShah/±arit/XX Festival /ITAmidah/XX./PR

/PR

/ITHoshanot/XX are traditionally recited on Sukkot after the readeròs repetition of
the /ITMusaf Amidah/XX. Because the /ITMusaf/XX and /ITShah/±arit Amidot/XX have been com-
bined into a single unit in this siddur, most congregations chant the
/ITHoshanot/XX as part of the service for taking out the Torah.    /SC/XXD.A.T./XX/PR

